    <title>Filter</title>
    <p>A Filter is used to amplify (boost), pass or attenuate (cut) defined parts of a frequency spectrum. Easy Effects uses the Filter from Calf Studio Gear.</p>
    <terms>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong" its:withinText="nested">Mode</em>
            </title>
            <p>The type of the filter.</p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong" its:withinText="nested">Frequency</em>
            </title>
            <p>The center or cut-off frequency of the filter.</p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong" its:withinText="nested">Resonance</em>
            </title>
            <p>Add an accentuation to the center frequency. When used on a bandpass the surrounding frequencies are decreased in level and the band gets more narrow. A bandreject is narrowed down to a thin needle.</p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong" its:withinText="nested">Inertia</em>
            </title>
            <p>Smooths the jumps between frequencies.</p>
        </item>
    </terms>
